out in the hall.

12:33.175 --> 12:34.709
Yes, ma'am!

12:34.777 --> 12:36.978
Mrs. Donaghy.

12:37.045 --> 12:38.379
You must be Jack's mother.

12:38.447 --> 12:39.480
Indeed, I am.

12:39.548 --> 12:42.417
And Jack has told me
so much about you.

12:42.484 --> 12:45.253
You're going to have
to work your backside,

12:45.320 --> 12:46.921
because chest-wise

12:46.989 --> 12:49.824
you have the measurements
of an altar boy.

12:49.892 --> 12:51.626
I wish Jack had told
me you were in town.

12:51.693 --> 12:54.395
Well, men have their
little secrets, don't they?

12:54.463 --> 12:55.830
Especially Jack.

12:55.898 --> 12:56.831
Secrets?

12:56.899 --> 12:58.266
What I'm trying to say is,

12:58.333 --> 12:59.934
if you're serious about Jackie,

13:00.002 --> 13:01.669
let him know now.

13:01.737 --> 13:04.806
A man like Jack has
other irons in the fire.

13:04.873 --> 13:05.973
I beg your pardon?

13:06.041 --> 13:08.576
Oh! Look at the time.

13:08.644 --> 13:12.914
I've got to get back to
calling Kenneth "carl"

13:12.981 --> 13:15.450
to see if he ever corrects me.

13:15.517 --> 13:17.118
Carl!

13:17.186 --> 13:18.519
Yes, ma'am?

13:22.724 --> 13:23.991
Lemon, have you seen Colleen?<,

13:24.059 --> 13:25.660
Kenneth was supposed
to be watching her,

13:25.727 --> 13:27.128
but I just saw him
with his eyes closed

13:27.196 --> 13:28.196
counting to infinity.

13:28.263 --> 13:30.164
You want to talk about moms, Jack?

13:30.232 --> 13:31.332
Listen to this.

13:31.400 --> 13:35.102
My mother could have
married buzz aldrin.

13:35.170 --> 13:36.170
Oh, really? I know buzz.

13:36.238 --> 13:37.572
We met at a photo shoot

13:37.639 --> 13:40.341
for <i>vanity fair's</i> annual
awesome gentleman issue.

13:40.409 --> 13:41.876
My mom blew it, Jack.

13:41.944 --> 13:44.378
She had true love,
and she threw it away

13:44.446 --> 13:46.547
just because it was inconvenient.

13:46.615 --> 13:48.349
Well, lemon, if your mom
had ended up with buzz,

13:48.417 --> 13:49.550
you would have never been born.

13:49.618 --> 13:52.386
Or I would have been
born Peter aldrin.

13:52.454 --> 13:54.856
And I+d wait for a woman
with the right stuff.

13:54.923 --> 13:56.257
Now, remember, in this scenario,

13:56.325 --> 13:57.992
I'm a man and my
father is an astronaut.

13:58.060 --> 13:59.360
Well, lemon, if you'd like to see

13:59.428 --> 14:00.695
what your mom's life
would have been,

14:00.762 --> 14:01.829
I can arrange for you to meet buzz.

14:01.897 --> 14:03.364
Are you serious? He's in town.

14:03.432 --> 14:05.566
I saw him last night at Rupert
Murdoch's twister party.

14:05.634 --> 14:09.504
I mean, uh, regular party.

14:09.571 --> 14:12.974
Tracy, this mother's day
thing is a disaster.

14:13.041 --> 14:14.041
I hear you.

14:14.109 --> 14:15.376
Because you're talking in the ear

14:15.444 --> 14:16.644
that I didn't lose a button in.

14:16.712 --> 14:19.847
I thought verna and I had
made this breakthrough,

14:19.915 --> 14:20.915
but now we're just back

14:20.983 --> 14:22.183
to fighting about
money and clothes.

14:22.251 --> 14:23.718
Thank God Terry's dead,

14:23.785 --> 14:25.419
or we'd be fighting
over him again too.

14:25.487 --> 14:28.556
Boy, I thought I had it
bad with my fake mom.

14:28.624 --> 14:29.657
Are you kidding?

14:29.725 --> 14:30.791
At least your fake mom

14:30.859 --> 14:32.360
has to act like she
cares about you.

14:32.427 --> 14:33.794
Yeah, it's true.

14:33.862 --> 14:35.062
And she is a good actress.

14:35.130 --> 14:37.398
I bought those pajamaralls.

14:37.466 --> 14:38.699
And you got to choose her.

14:38.767 --> 14:42.203
No, Jenna, no one gets
to choose their mom...

14:42.271 --> 14:43.638
Even when they're fake.

14:43.705 --> 14:45.039
For good or bad,

14:45.107 --> 14:46.240
we're stuck with them.

14:46.308 --> 14:47.708
And you know what?

14:47.776 --> 14:50.177
They don't get to choose
who we are, either.

14:50.245 --> 14:52.580
And God knows we're not perfect.

14:52.648 --> 14:54.115
It's true.

14:54.182 --> 14:58.653
Sometimes I sing too beautifully.

14:58.720 --> 14:59.954
What a nice surpri--

15:00.022 --> 15:01.389
is there another woman?

15:01.456 --> 15:03.624
What? How did you--? Colleen.

15:03.692 --> 15:04.926
Don't blame your mother, Jack.

15:04.993 --> 15:06.260
This is about us.

15:06.328 --> 15:09.063
Oh, my God. Look, Avery,
you know how I feel.

15:09.131 --> 15:11.232
So I'm gonna skip the part
where I deny anything.

15:11.300 --> 15:13.534
Then you skip the part
where you yell at me.

15:13.602 --> 15:16.971
And then we both move on to the,
uh, make-up sex.

15:17.039 --> 15:17.972
Wow.

15:18.040 --> 15:19.373
That is a swing.

15:19.441 --> 15:22.710
Look, I assumed you
and I were exclusive,

15:22.778 --> 15:24.412
but we never talked about it,

15:24.479 --> 15:27.448
so maybe this is partly my fault.

15:27.516 --> 15:29.250
And I forgive you. Come here.

15:29.318 --> 15:30.985
I'm sorry.

15:31.053 --> 15:33.888
But these tactics have
worked on stupider women.

15:33.956 --> 15:35.489
If we're going to move forward,

15:35.557 --> 15:38.926
you better figure out
what it is you want.

15:38.994 --> 15:41.095
Soon.

15:43.899 --> 15:46.400
Excuse me, Dr. aldrin.

15:46.468 --> 15:48.102
I'm sorry. There wasn't a door,
so I just...

15:48.170 --> 15:49.270
I don't believe in barriers,

15:49.338 --> 15:51.405
because I always break them.

15:51.473 --> 15:52.440
You must be Liz.

15:52.507 --> 15:53.574
Yes, sir.

15:53.642 --> 15:56.344
I actually came about my mother,
Margaret lemon.

15:56.411 --> 15:58.613
Well, you would have known
her as Margaret Freeman.

15:58.680 --> 16:01.315
Maggie Freeman?
Of course I remember her.

16:01.383 --> 16:02.550
Well, I'm sorry to bother you,

16:02.618 --> 16:05.152
but I can't help but
wonder what my mom lost

16:05.220 --> 16:06.954
by giving up on you,

16:07.022 --> 16:08.723
her perfect man.

16:08.790 --> 16:10.791
Perfect? Sure,
I'm a famous astronaut,

16:10.859 --> 16:15.429
decorated fighter pilot,
doctorate from mit,

16:15.497 --> 16:17.598
but even I sometimes...

16:17.666 --> 16:20.001
I see you. I see what you're doing.

16:20.068 --> 16:23.838
Return to the night.
You've no business here.

16:23.905 --> 16:25.506
Are you yelling at the moon?

16:25.574 --> 16:27.541
I'm sorry. She and I just...

16:27.609 --> 16:29.977
I get mad sometimes.

16:30.045 --> 16:31.245
Sure.

16:31.313 --> 16:33.247
Look, you want to know
what your mother missed?

16:33.315 --> 16:36.050
Years of drinking,
depression, cheating.

16:36.118 --> 16:39.286
I flipped over a saab in
the San Fernando valley.

16:39.354 --> 16:42.223
I once woke up in the
air and space museum

16:42.290 --> 16:45.660
with a revolver in the
waistband of my Jean shorts.

16:45.727 --> 16:47.528
Oh, my God. But you're--

16:47.596 --> 16:48.729
a human being.

16:48.797 --> 16:50.297
But I'm at peace now.

16:50.365 --> 16:52.667
Sober almost 32 years.

16:52.734 --> 16:57.038
But I would have put Maggie
Freeman through hell.

16:58.607 --> 17:00.174
The moms were right.

17:00.242 --> 17:04.078
There's no such thing as
astronaut Mike Dexter.

17:04.146 --> 17:05.311
What am I doing?

17:05.380 --> 17:07.647
I'm sorry if I've disappointed you.

17:07.715 --> 17:10.751
Would you like to yell at
the moon with buzz aldrin?

17:10.819 --> 17:13.854
Yes, please.

17:13.922 --> 17:15.122
I own you!

17:15.190 --> 17:16.589
You dumb moon!

17:16.657 --> 17:18.291
I walked on your face!

17:18.359 --> 17:19.660
Don't you know it's day?

17:19.728 --> 17:22.063
Idiot!

17:22.130 --> 17:24.531
Well, I'm ready for the show.

17:24.598 --> 17:28.102
Mom, you're wearing my outfit.

17:28.170 --> 17:30.304
Well, a mother makes sacrifices.

17:30.372 --> 17:33.374
Like those 16 hours
I spent in labor,

17:33.442 --> 17:35.409
even though it was Margarita Monday

17:35.477 --> 17:38.012
at dockside Joe's.

17:38.080 --> 17:40.214
Daughters make sacrifices too.

17:40.282 --> 17:43.217
Why are you wearing that?
Who's paying you?

17:43.285 --> 17:44.752
No one.

17:44.820 --> 17:48.222
I'm wearing it for the same
reason you're wearing mine.

17:48.290 --> 17:50.324
Because I love you.

17:50.392 --> 17:53.127
I love you too, baby girl. Oh.

17:53.195 --> 17:54.862
Why does your chest feel weird?

17:54.930 --> 17:57.531
Uh, because I love you so much.

17:57.599 --> 18:02.303
♪ Sincerely ♪

18:02.370 --> 18:08.309
♪ oh yes sincerely ♪

18:08.376 --> 18:13.881
♪ 'cause I love you so dearly ♪

18:13.949 --> 18:16.517
you look beautiful... Mom.

18:16.585 --> 18:18.419
Thank you.

18:18.487 --> 18:20.321
Son.

18:20.388 --> 18:24.959
I think I'm ready for the sex talk.

18:25.026 --> 18:30.898
♪ Oh you know how I love you ♪

18:30.966 --> 18:34.568
mom, you were right to settle.

18:34.636 --> 18:35.903
I'm glad you married dad.

18:35.971 --> 18:37.671
So am I, dear.

18:37.739 --> 18:40.441
Now, would you please
find yourself someone

18:40.509 --> 18:41.776
and start a family

18:41.843 --> 18:45.579
before my hereditary
dementia sets in?

18:45.647 --> 18:46.580
Wait, what?

18:46.648 --> 18:48.949
♪ Please say ♪

18:49.017 --> 18:55.322
♪ you'll be mine ♪

18:55.390 --> 18:58.592
you.

18:58.660 --> 19:00.227
What is wrong with you?

19:00.295 --> 19:01.629
I am 51 years old.

19:01.696 --> 19:02.863
Do you not think I can take care

19:02.931 --> 19:04.231
of my own personal life?

19:04.299 --> 19:05.766
Think? I know you can't.

19:05.834 --> 19:07.535
You do a lot of things well--

19:07.602 --> 19:10.838
make money, choose wine, wear ties.

19:10.906 --> 19:13.574
But you and women? Disaster.

19:13.642 --> 19:15.442
Divorce. Broken engagements.

19:15.510 --> 19:17.144
I assume herpes.

19:17.212 --> 19:18.546
And I wonder why I'm like that.

19:18.613 --> 19:19.947
Maybe it's because you can't let go

19:20.015 --> 19:21.549
of your precious Jackie,

19:21.616 --> 19:23.217
so you undermine me at every turn.

19:23.285 --> 19:24.985
I'm not gonna be around forever.

19:25.053 --> 19:26.487
Don't pull that out, Colleen.

19:26.555 --> 19:28.589
And if I don't do something,

19:28.657 --> 19:30.391
you will never make a decision.

19:30.458 --> 19:34.762
You'll just froufrou
around with Nancy and Avery

19:34.830 --> 19:36.530
until they're both gone.

19:36.598 --> 19:38.065
And then where will I be?

19:38.133 --> 19:41.502
I'll be circling the globe
in my coffin rocket.

19:41.570 --> 19:43.604
Something I saw on tv.

19:43.672 --> 19:44.738
It's very expensive.

19:44.806 --> 19:47.775
I'm done disapproving, Jackie.

19:47.843 --> 19:50.110
I'm just trying to help.

19:50.178 --> 19:53.147
I need to know that someone

19:53.215 --> 19:55.616
is looking out for my little boy.

19:55.684 --> 19:57.685
All right, Colleen.

19:57.752 --> 20:01.155
Then I'm asking you,
for the first time in my life,

20:01.223 --> 20:03.691
tell me what to do.

20:03.758 --> 20:05.726
And I'm going to tell you,

20:05.794 --> 20:09.597
for the first time in my life,

20:09.664 --> 20:12.066
I can't!

20:14.202 --> 20:15.870
I--I did not lose her, sir.

20:15.937 --> 20:18.405
Carl would never let you down.

20:18.473 --> 20:19.974
Carl, that does not sound right.

20:20.041 --> 20:22.476
Kevin--no.

20:22.544 --> 20:25.446
Who am I?

20:25.513 --> 20:27.147
Is it Keith?

20:27.215 --> 20:28.549
No, that's not-- yes, I'm Keith.

20:32.787 --> 20:35.422
That's our show.
Thanks for watching.

20:35.490 --> 20:36.724
But before you go to bed,

20:36.791 --> 20:39.793
our moms are gonna tuck you
in with a special song.

20:39.861 --> 20:43.397
♪ Don't go to sleep with
a frown in your pocket ♪

20:43.465 --> 20:47.401
♪ take it to the yard
and tie it to a rocket ♪

20:47.469 --> 20:48.836
♪ shoot it to the moon ♪

20:48.904 --> 20:50.838
♪ you'll feel better soon ♪

20:50.906 --> 20:54.808
♪ don't go to bed with a frown ♪

20:54.876 --> 21:02.116
♪ don't go to bed with a frown ♪

